it's incredibly popular
easy to learn and use
can be used for a very wide range of applications
code can be executed on the client side, which reduces the load on the server
we have to worry about browser support
we have to be more securoty-conscious :
* the client has a copy of our source code
* third party code can make our site more vulnerable
certain parts of the language can behave very strangely
not the bedt language for "Object-oriencted purists"
as a language , JS is evolving very quickly

pros                                  vs           cons
*popularity                                     * browser-support
* simplicity                                    * security
* multi-platform                                * language oddities
*client-side execution                          * not great for OOP
                                                * rapid change
